excerpt: Aquarium with species from the Red Sea, plus dolphin shows, an auditorium & sports club with a pool.
detail_description: Fakieh Aquarium is a must-visit destination for those seeking an immersive experience with marine life. Located in Jeddah, Saudi Arabia, it is the only public aquarium in the country and boasts over 200 species of sea creatures from the Red Sea. Visitors can marvel at sharks, groupers, string rays, napoleon wrasse, sea horses, green turtles, and more. The aquarium plans to expand its collection to include even more fascinating underwater residents like the sea dragon.
name: Fakieh Aquarium
address: Al Kurnaysh Br Rd, Next to, Al Kuranaysh Rd, Jeddah 23413, Saudi Arabia

excerpt: Al-Balad, also known as Jeddah Historic District, is the historical area of Jeddah, the second largest city of Saudi Arabia. Al-Balad can literally be translated to "The Town". Al-Balad is the historic center of the City of Jeddah. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Al-Balad, also known as Jeddah Historic District, is the old town area of Jeddah, Saudi Arabia. Its name translates to 'The Town.' This historical neighborhood was designated as a UNESCO World Heritage site in 2014, making it one of five such sites in the country.
name: Al-Balad
address: Jeddah, Saudi Arabia

excerpt: Seawater is ejected some 200 m. from this massive fountain that can be seen from around the city.
detail_description: King Fahad's Fountain, also known as the Jeddah Fountain, is a must-visit attraction located in Jeddah, Saudi Arabia. It holds the title of being the world's tallest water fountain and can be seen from various parts of the city. Donated by King Fahd, it was constructed between 1980 and 1983 and launched in 1985.
name: King Fahad's Fountain
address: Meeza International Tourism Services Co. Ltd, Al Andalus, Jeddah 23311, Saudi Arabia

detail_description: Cenomi Mall of Arabia is a massive 261,000 square meter shopping destination located near the King Abdulaziz International Airport in Jeddah. It boasts an impressive lineup of global fashion brands including Zara, Forever 21, Debenhams, DKNY, and Ted Baker. The mall also offers a variety of dining options ranging from fast food favorites like Burger King and Pizza Hut to fine restaurants such as Fridays and Smith & Wollensky.
name: Cenomi Mall of Arabia
address: Al-Madinah Al-Munawarah Rd, An Nuzhah, Jeddah 23532, Saudi Arabia

excerpt: Vibrant retail hub featuring shops, casual dining, a cinema & a fun center with bowling & billiards.
detail_description: Red Sea Mall in Jeddah is a vibrant retail hub offering a unique shopping experience, casual dining options, a cinema, and a fun center with bowling and billiards. This mall is not just about shopping; it also provides a historical encounter with its dedicated section showcasing the country's proud heritage and culture. The traditional decor and paintings of historical figures add to the cultural attraction of the mall.
name: Red Sea Mall
address: طريق الملك عبدالعزيز،, Ash Shati, Jeddah 21146, Saudi Arabia

excerpt: Amusement park offering roller coasters & rides, a silk museum, ice skating & global dining.
detail_description: Al Shallal Theme Park in Jeddah is a must-visit destination for families and thrill-seekers. This popular amusement park offers a wide range of attractions, including roller coasters, educational boat rides, and gravity-defying experiences like zero gravity. The lively vibes and joyfulness make it a top choice for tourists visiting Saudi Arabia.
name: Al Shallal Theme Park
address: Al Kurnaysh Br Rd, Ash Shati, Jeddah 23413, Saudi Arabia

excerpt: Former 19th-century mansion, now a museum & cultural center presenting exhibitions & lectures.
detail_description: Nassif House Museum, located in the heart of an archaeological palace, is a former 19th-century mansion that has been transformed into a museum and cultural center. The museum boasts an impressive collection of archaeological tools, historical kitchen utensils, pottery artifacts, and antique photographs from a bygone era. Once the residence of King Abdul Aziz, the building features intricate sculptures and an elegant facade.
name: Nassif House Museum
address: F5MQ+M32, Al Dhahab, Al-Balad, Jeddah 22236, Saudi Arabia

detail_description: Al Rahma Mosque, located on the coast of the Red Sea in Jeddah, is a stunning blend of modern and traditional Islamic architecture. The mosque's marble structure and intricately tiled prayer halls make it a sight to behold for both Muslims and non-Muslims. Known as the 'floating mosque,' its stilted setting creates an illusion of floating on the ocean during high tide, especially at sunrise or sunset.
name: Al Rahma Mosque
address: 3021 Hael, Al Andalus, JERA6978, 6978, Jeddah 23431, Saudi Arabia

excerpt: Museum complex highlighting the city's heritage, with a mosque, relics & traditional architecture.
detail_description: Al Taybat International City Museum of Science and Information is a vast museum complex located in Jeddah's Al-Faisaliyah district. It showcases the rich history of the city and the Arabian Peninsula, featuring traditional Hijazi architectural style with ornate minarets. The museum houses an extensive collection of international Islamic artifacts, including ancient coins, modern furniture, Islamic scripts, ethnic attires, old currencies, and antique earthenware.
name: Al Taybat International City Museum of Science and Information
address: 3170 Raihanat Al Jazirah, Al Faisaliyyah, District, Jeddah 23442, Saudi Arabia

detail_description: The Jeddah waterfront, also known as the Jeddah Corniche, is a renowned destination in the Middle East. It is celebrated for its stunning beauty and serene atmosphere. The expansive promenade offers a delightful array of cafes and dining options, making it a popular choice for visitors. The area's remarkable architecture includes notable landmarks such as the Nawras sculpture and Tawheed mosque.
name: Jeddah waterfront
address: J425+W4C, Ash Shati, Jeddah 23511, Saudi Arabia

detail_description: Al Saif Beach, located in Jeddah, Saudi Arabia, is a popular destination for both locals and tourists. It offers a peaceful and calm ambiance, making it perfect for family picnics and water adventures. Visitors can enjoy activities such as swimming, water sports, horseback riding, and buggy rentals. The beach is known for its stunning sunrise and mesmerizing sunset views.
name: Al Saif Beach
address: Jeddah 22713, Saudi Arabia

excerpt: Venerable amusement park with indoor/outdoor rides & games, plus an ice skating rink & a food court.
detail_description: Atallah Happy Land Park is a renowned amusement park located in the heart of Jeddah, offering a diverse range of indoor and outdoor entertainment for visitors of all ages. The park features various themed areas, including a 3-D cinema, arcade game zone, and bowling alley. With around 30 exciting rides such as Skyloop, Surfrider, Space Gun, and Big Wheel, there's something for everyone.
name: Atallah Happy Land Park
address: حي, 2763 Al Kurnaysh Br Rd, Ash Shati, JEBC6263، 6263, Jeddah 23611, Saudi Arabia

detail_description: Historic District, also known as Al-Balad, is the oldest tourist destination in Jeddah, Saudi Arabia. Its narrow alleys and traditional houses with unique architectural features offer a glimpse into the area's rich history. Visitors can explore historic sites such as Naseef House and Al-Shafee Mosque. The district has been carefully restored to showcase its old-world charm, making it a perfect spot for photographers and history enthusiasts alike.
name: Historic District
address: F5PQ+734, Al-Balad, Unnamed Road, Jeddah 22236, Saudi Arabia

detail_description: Silver Sands Beach is a stunning private beach located in Jeddah along the Red Sea. It boasts azure blue waters, long sandy coastlines, and breathtaking views of the lush surroundings, making it a popular destination for tourists. Visitors can relax on comfortable beach chairs, enjoy water sports like windsurfing and snorkeling, or take a dip in the cool turquoise waters. The beach also features an onsite cafe where guests can grab a light meal and drinks.
name: Silver Sands Beach
address: Prince Abdullah AlFiasal St, Al Lulu, Jeddah 23821, Saudi Arabia

excerpt: Landmark port lighthouse & observation tower with a distinctively modern, Islamic-influenced design.
detail_description: The Jeddah Port Lighthouse, also known as the Jeddah Light, is a remarkable landmark with a modern design influenced by Islamic architecture. Standing at 436 feet tall, it holds the title of the world's tallest lighthouse and is located at the northern entrance of Jeddah Seaport. While access to the seaport itself is restricted, visitors can still enjoy stunning views of the lighthouse from nearby areas such as Corniche Commercial Center and Central Fish Market.
name: Jeddah Port Lighthouse
address: F49X+CW7، ميناء جدة الإسلامي،, Saudi Arabia

detail_description: Nestled in the historic Al Balad city of Jeddah, Souq Al Alawi is a charming old market that exudes Arabian folklore. The ancient buildings and towering balconies create a picturesque setting for visitors to explore. Here, one can find a wide array of goods including antique souvenirs, textiles, spices, silver and gold jewelry, as well as regional delicacies.
name: Souq Al Alawi
address: Al-Balad, Jeddah 22236, Saudi Arabia

name: Fakieh Planetarium
address: located in, Al Shallal Theme Park, Ash Shati, Jeddah 23413, Saudi Arabia

detail_description: Bait Al Balad, located in the historic neighborhood of Al Balad in Jeddah, is a museum housed in a building that once served as the British Legions headquarters. The museum showcases a diverse collection of antiquities from both Islamic and pre-Islamic eras, including furniture, handicrafts, tools, artifacts, and photographs documenting Jeddah's history.
name: Bait Al Balad
address: F5QM+432, الكنداسه, Al-Balad, Jeddah 22233, Saudi Arabia

detail_description: Jeddah Promenade, also known as the Art Promenade, is a unique and vibrant area in the city of Jeddah. This waterfront neighborhood offers a range of experiences and attractions that set it apart from other metropolises. Visitors can enjoy international events at the marina, take leisurely walks to the Jeddah Yacht Club, and relax with drinks at Celsius 95. Families will appreciate the playground for kids and the option to rent scooters for exploring.
name: Jeddah Promenade
address: 8625 2212 طريق الكورنيش،, Ash Shati, Jeddah 23612, Saudi Arabia

detail_description: Al Rahma Masjed, also known as the Floating Mosque, is located just west of Jeddah airport. It is admired for its beautiful design and cleanliness. The mosque has two floors and includes a section for female worshippers. However, visitors have noted that there is limited parking available. Despite this, many people appreciate the mosque's beauty and find it to be an excellent place for prayer.
name: Al Rahma Masjed
address: 2726 6722 Ouqbah Ibn Nafeh, Al Sharafeyah, Jeddah 23216, Saudi Arabia
